## Git Workflow

This is the `personal`-repo crew workflow.

- Small fixes may go straight to `main`: research the issue, fix it, commit it,
  and push it.
- Slightly larger work may use a branch for iteration, then merge locally (for
  example with `--ff` when appropriate) and push `main` once ready.
- Integration branches are also allowed when that is the chosen workflow for the
  current line of work.
- The important point is to follow normal development discipline without
  requiring a PR workflow by default.

If it is not already obvious which path applies, decide it explicitly with the
human before landing the work.

